The paper presents a computational model for processing dynamic spatial relations in an embodied robotic interaction setup, which involves natural language processing, cognitive semantics, and spatial representation and reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, which covers artificial intelligence and its subfields, including natural language processing and cognitive modeling. The second likely sub-category is cs.RO, which covers robotics and automation, as the paper focuses on embodied robotic interaction. The third likely sub-category is cs.CL, which covers computation and language, as the paper involves natural language processing. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.LG, which covers machine learning, as the paper presents a computational model. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CV, which covers computer vision, as the paper involves processing visual information from the environment.
